                        <img src="/images/photo-white-building-pink-hydrangeas-garden.webp" alt="Beautiful garden and home protected by seamless guttering" class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200" />
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-gray-50">
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
                
                <div class="mb-16">
                    <div class="reveal flex items-center mb-8">
                        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-dark rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 11H5m14 0a2 2 0 012 2v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2v-6a2 2 0 012-2m14 0V9a2 2 0 00-2-2M5 11V9a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h6a2 2 0 012 2v2M7 7h10"></path></svg>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-extrabold text-brand-dark">The Product</h3>
                    </div>

                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="reveal bg-white rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-heading text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-3">What exactly is seamless aluminium guttering?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                                Seamless aluminium guttering is formed from a continuous coil of heavy-duty aluminium. Using our mobile extrusion machine, we roll out a single, uninterrupted length of guttering measured exactly to the span of your roofline. Because there are no seams or joined sections along the straight runs, the primary cause of gutter leaks is entirely eliminated.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-100 bg-white rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-heading text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-3">How long will an aluminium guttering system last?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                                Aluminium is incredibly durable and naturally highly resistant to corrosion and rust. Under standard UK weather conditions, a professionally installed seamless aluminium system can reliably last upwards of 30 years, drastically outperforming standard plastic uPVC gutters which become brittle and perish over time.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-200 bg-white rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-heading text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-3">Do you offer different colours and finishes?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                                Yes, we do. Our aluminium coil is finished with a factory-applied, highly durable powder coating that will not flake or peel. We offer several standard colours, including <strong class="text-brand-dark">Black, White, Anthracite Grey, and Brown</strong>, ensuring a perfect aesthetic match for both modern builds and traditional Lancashire stone properties.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="mb-16">
                    <div class="reveal flex items-center mb-8">
                        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-dark rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14.121 14.121L19 19m-7-7l7-7m-7 7l-2.879 2.879M12 12L9.121 9.121m0 5.758a3 3 0 10-4.243-4.243 3 3 0 004.243 4.243z"></path></svg>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-extrabold text-brand-dark">Installation Process</h3>
                    </div>

                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="reveal bg-white rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-heading text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-3">How long does the installation take?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                                Because we extrude the guttering on-site, our process is incredibly efficient. For most standard domestic properties (such as a typical 3-bedroom semi-detached home), we can safely remove your old system and fully install the new seamless aluminium system within a single working day.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-100 bg-white rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-heading text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-3">Do I need to be at home during the installation?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                                No, as long as we have clear, unrestricted external access to all sides of your property where work is required, you do not need to be present. We will handle the entire installation and clean up the site thoroughly before we leave.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-200 bg-white rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-heading text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-3">What happens to my old guttering?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                                We provide a complete end-to-end service. Our team will safely dismantle your old plastic or cast iron guttering and remove it from your property, disposing of all materials responsibly and recycling where possible.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <div class="reveal flex items-center mb-8">
                        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-dark rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17.657 16.657L13.414 20.9a1.998 1.998 0 01-2.827 0l-4.244-4.243a8 8 0 1111.314 0z"></path></svg>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-extrabold text-brand-dark">Pricing & Logistics</h3>
                    </div>

                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="reveal bg-white rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-heading text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-3">Are seamless gutters much more expensive than plastic?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                                While the initial investment is slightly higher than off-the-shelf plastic uPVC, the long-term value is vastly superior. Seamless aluminium is a premium product that requires virtually zero maintenance and eliminates the need for frequent, costly repairs caused by leaking joints. It pays for itself over its 30+ year lifespan.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-100 bg-white rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-heading text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-3">What areas in the UK do you cover?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                                Our headquarters is based at Pine Garth Farm in Colne, Lancashire. Our standard service area covers the surrounding regions across the Lancashire and Yorkshire borders. This includes <strong class="text-brand-dark">Colne, Skipton, Burnley, Barrowford, Earby, and Keighley.</strong> If you live slightly outside these areas, please call us to check availability.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-200 bg-white rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                            <h4 class="font-heading text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-3">Do you offer free quotes?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                                Absolutely. We offer a completely free, no-obligation site survey. We will visit your property, take precise measurements, discuss your requirements, and provide a transparent, fixed-price quotation.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </section>

